;British Airways World Cargo Fleet
* 3 [[Boeing 747-8F]] (operated by [[Global Supply Systems]] in BA livery)

Other aircraft types used between 1974 and 1983 were [[Vickers Vanguard|Vickers 953C]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.airliners.net/photo/British-Airways-Cargo/Vickers-953C-Merchantman/1993917/&sid=c4e8ea1c4a152b3c8c48af0e7fe3bb87 |title=BA Cargo Vickers 963C |publisher=Airliners.net |date=9 October 2011 |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref> Boeing 707-300C <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.airliners.net/photo/British-Airways-Cargo/Boeing-707-336C/1809358/&sid=e45ef314a4882b44d8b2bcf93e63268b |title=BA Cargo 707-330C |publisher=Airliners.net |date=6 May 1980 |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref> and [[Boeing 747-200F]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.airliners.net/photo/British-Airways-Cargo/Boeing-747-236F-SCD/0136126/&sid=2a3bcc03830c9190ff29236f7e117c3d |title=BA Cargo 747-200F |publisher=Airliners.net |date=21 January 2001 |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref> while the [[Boeing 747-400F]] was operated from the 1990s to 2001 through [[Atlas Air]] and 2002 to early 2012 by Global Supply Systems, of these only one of Atlas Air's aircraft wore BA livery,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.airliners.net/photo/British-Airways-World/Boeing-747-47UF-SCD/0051691/&sid=8ce10b521ee5c89ec69c2f762f5bf4ac |title=BA Cargo World Tails 747-400F |publisher=Airliners.net |date=23 October 1999 |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref> the others flew in Atlas and Global Supply's own colours.

